OL,3,CNewcastle City Council budget: Tax
OL,4,Crises and #15million of cuts approved
OL,6,FCouncil cabinet member Paul Frew told
OL,7,Fthis week's annual budget meeting that
OL,8,Fthere was "no low-hanging fruit" left
OL,9,Fat the civic centre that could be
OL,10,Ftargeted for cuts after #369 million
OL,11,Fwas slashed over 14 years. However, he
OL,12,Finsisted Newcastle was in a "much
OL,13,Fbetter position than comparable local
OL,14,Fauthorities".
OL,16,FNick Kemp, the council's leader,
OL,17,Fwarned that local councils had been
OL,18,Fplunged into an "existential crisis"
OL,19,Fand that the model to fund council
OL,20,Fservices "simply does not work".
